 imitate his shining example, with lavishly illuminated copies being made for members of his own family and other noble readers.This first English translation of the text, accompanied by an introduction and extensive notes based on new research into both archival and literary sources, aims to offer the reader an in-depth portrayal of Lalaing in the context of the chivalric, dynastic and political culture of his day.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aBibliography & Manuscripts. 4aMedieval History. 4aMilitary History. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aBurgundian court.  aChivalric biography.  aCrusade.  aDynastic culture.  aFeats of arms.  aJousts.  aKnight.  aLate Middle Ages.  aMilitary leader.  aPolitical culture.1 aBrown-Grant, Rosalind, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDamen, Mario, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311143099740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781800105928?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781800105928423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781800105928/original  a978-3-11-143099-7  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles